Class QueueSorter

java.lang.Object
  QueueSorter

public class QueueSorter
extends Object

This class will act as a Priority queue for ElevatorQueues. It will sort the Queues based on their sizes and allows for easy computation of the location where the most passengers are waiting

public boolean add(ElevatorQueue eq)
Adds a new ElevatorQueue to this PQ if there is room. Returns true if the addition was successful and false if it wasn't (no room). The Elevator Queue added will be placed in order of it's size

moveUp

private void moveUp(int indx)

remove

public ElevatorQueue remove()
Removes the ElevatorQueue with greatest priority from this group, restoring order to the heap afterwards

Returns:
the ElevatorQueue of biggest size, null if Queue is empty

moveDown

private void moveDown(int indx)
This method will compare the element at the given index with it's children. If it has less priority than either of it's children it will swap with the child (which ever of the 2 has a greater priority) It will then recursively call moveDown on the new child element to continue restoring heapOrder

Parameters:
indx - - index of desired element to compare to child

getNext

public ElevatorQueue getNext()
Returns the next ElevatorQueue in the priority queue. the ElevatorQueue is not removed from the group.

the next ElevatorQueue or null if the group is empty
